    "course_title": "EXPERIMENTS AND CAUSAL METHODS FOR BUSINESS INSIGHTS",
    "description": "Provides an introduction to experimental and causal methods for driving business insights. Topics include: (1) Review and distinction of correlation vs. causation; (2) design and analysis of randomized-controlled experiments; and (3) identification of \"natural experiments\" in business data and corresponding empirical strategies.",
